cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a deep learning framework for detecting temporal transitions in functional MRI data without explicit modeling assumptions. This involves using recurrent neural networks for sequence modeling and anomaly detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) due to the use of neural networks. The paper also involves analyzing and processing data, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
